.TH "cdu" "1" "2026-07-20" "" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
cdu - Fast disk usage analyzer with a Charm interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]cdu [flags] [directory_to_scan]\f[R]
.PP
\f[B]cdu themes\f[R] | \f[B]cdu update\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
cdu is a fast disk usage analyzer.
It is a fork of gdu (https://github.com/dundee/gdu) by Daniel Milde: the
disk-analysis engine is gdu\[cq]s, unchanged, and cdu replaces the
interactive interface with one built on the Charm stack, adding themes,
recoverable deletes, multi-select, and a self-updater.
.PP
The non-interactive and JSON export modes are byte-for-byte identical to
gdu\[cq]s, and \f[B]--classic\f[R] gives you gdu\[cq]s original
interface.
This is not the official gdu \[em] report cdu\[cq]s own bugs at
https://github.com/pottom/cdu/issues.
.PP
cdu is intended primarily for SSD disks where it can fully utilize
parallel processing.
HDDs work as well, but the performance gain is not so huge.
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
\f[B]-h\f[R], \f[B]--help\f[R][=false] help for cdu
.PP
\f[B]--classic\f[R][=false] Use gdu\[cq]s original interface instead of
the Charm one
.PP
\f[B]--theme\f[R]=\[dq]\[dq] Color theme for the Charm interface (charm,
midnight, ember, phosphor, mono, or a user theme).
See \f[B]cdu themes\f[R].
.PP
\f[B]--icons\f[R][=false] Show Nerd Font file icons (needs a patched
font)
.PP
\f[B]--info\f[R][=true] Show the item-info pane at the foot of the list
(toggle with i)
.PP
\f[B]-i\f[R], \f[B]--ignore-dirs\f[R]=[/proc,/dev,/sys,/run] Paths to
ignore (separated by comma).
Supports both absolute and relative paths.
.PP
\f[B]-I\f[R], \f[B]--ignore-dirs-pattern\f[R] Path patterns to ignore
(separated by comma).
Supports both absolute and relative path patterns.
.PP
\f[B]-X\f[R], \f[B]--ignore-from\f[R] Read path patterns to ignore from
file.
Supports both absolute and relative path patterns.
.PP
\f[B]-T\f[R], \f[B]--type\f[R] File types to include (e.g., \[en]type
yaml,json)
.PP
\f[B]-E\f[R], \f[B]--exclude-type\f[R] File types to exclude (e.g.,
\[en]exclude-type yaml,json)
.PP
\f[B]--max-age\f[R] Include files with mtime no older than DURATION
(e.g., 7d, 2h30m, 1y2mo)
.PP
\f[B]--min-age\f[R] Include files with mtime at least DURATION old
(e.g., 30d, 1w)
.PP
\f[B]--since\f[R] Include files with mtime >= WHEN.
WHEN accepts RFC3339 timestamp (e.g., 2025-08-11T01:00:00-07:00) or date
only YYYY-MM-DD (calendar-day compare; includes the whole day)
.PP
\f[B]--until\f[R] Include files with mtime <= WHEN.
WHEN accepts RFC3339 timestamp or date only YYYY-MM-DD
.PP
\f[B]-l\f[R], \f[B]--log-file\f[R]=\[dq]/dev/null\[dq] Path to a logfile
.PP
\f[B]-m\f[R], \f[B]--max-cores\f[R] Set max cores that cdu will use.
.PP
\f[B]-c\f[R], \f[B]--no-color\f[R][=false] Do not use colorized output
.PP
\f[B]-x\f[R], \f[B]--no-cross\f[R][=false] Do not cross filesystem
boundaries
.PP
\f[B]-H\f[R], \f[B]--no-hidden\f[R][=false] Ignore hidden directories
(beginning with dot)
.PP
\f[B]-L\f[R], \f[B]--follow-symlinks\f[R][=false] Follow symlinks for
files, i.e.\ show the size of the file to which symlink points to
(symlinks to directories are not followed)
.PP
\f[B]-n\f[R], \f[B]--non-interactive\f[R][=false] Do not run in
interactive mode
.PP
\f[B]--interactive\f[R][=false] Force interactive mode even when output
is not a TTY
.PP
\f[B]-p\f[R], \f[B]--no-progress\f[R][=false] Do not show progress in
non-interactive mode
.PP
\f[B]-u\f[R], \f[B]--no-unicode\f[R][=false] Do not use Unicode symbols
(for size bar)
.PP
\f[B]-s\f[R], \f[B]--summarize\f[R][=false] Show only a total in
non-interactive mode
.PP
\f[B]-t\f[R], \f[B]--top\f[R][=0] Show only top X largest files in
non-interactive mode
.PP
\f[B]-d\f[R], \f[B]--show-disks\f[R][=false] Show all mounted disks
.PP
\f[B]-a\f[R], \f[B]--show-apparent-size\f[R][=false] Show apparent size
.PP
\f[B]-C\f[R], \f[B]--show-item-count\f[R][=false] Show number of items
in directory
.PP
\f[B]-k\f[R], \f[B]--show-in-kib\f[R][=false] Show sizes in KiB (or kB
with \[en]si) in non-interactive mode
.PP
\f[B]-M\f[R], \f[B]--show-mtime\f[R][=false] Show latest mtime of items
in directory
.PP
\f[B]--archive-browsing\f[R][=false] Enable browsing of zip/jar/tar
archives (tar, tar.gz, tar.bz2, tar.xz)
.PP
\f[B]--depth\f[R][=0] Show directory structure up to specified depth in
non-interactive mode (0 means the flag is ignored)
.PP
\f[B]--collapse-path\f[R][=false] Collapse single-child directory chains
.PP
\f[B]--mouse\f[R][=false] Use mouse
.PP
\f[B]--si\f[R][=false] Show sizes with decimal SI prefixes (kB, MB, GB)
instead of binary prefixes (KiB, MiB, GiB)
.PP
\f[B]--no-prefix\f[R][=false] Show sizes as raw numbers without any
prefixes (SI or binary) in non-interactive mode
.PP
\f[B]--no-spawn-shell\f[R][=false] Do not allow spawning shell
.PP
\f[B]--no-delete\f[R][=false] Do not allow deletions
.PP
\f[B]--no-view-file\f[R][=false] Do not allow viewing file contents
.PP
\f[B]-f\f[R], \f[B]--input-file\f[R] Import analysis from JSON file.
If the file is \[dq]-\[dq], read from standard input.
.PP
\f[B]-o\f[R], \f[B]--output-file\f[R] Export all info into file as JSON.
If the file is \[dq]-\[dq], write to standard output.
.PP
\f[B]--config-file\f[R] Read config from file.
Without it, cdu reads $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/cdu/cdu.yaml
(\[ti]/.config/cdu/cdu.yaml), falling back read-only to an existing gdu
config and saying so.
.PP
\f[B]--write-config\f[R][=false] Write the current configuration to
\[ti]/.config/cdu/cdu.yaml (or \f[B]--config-file\f[R]).
This is also how you take over a gdu config.
.PP
\f[B]--enable-profiling\f[R][=false] Enable collection of profiling data
and provide it on http://localhost:6060/debug/pprof/
.PP
\f[B]-D\f[R], \f[B]--db\f[R] Store analysis in database (\f[I].sqlite
for SQLite, \f[R].badger for BadgerDB)
.PP
\f[B]-r\f[R], \f[B]--read-from-storage\f[R][=false] Use existing
database instead of re-scanning
.PP
\f[B]-v\f[R], \f[B]--version\f[R][=false] Print version (cdu\[cq]s, and
the gdu engine it embeds)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\f[B]cdu themes\f[R]
List the bundled color themes, each drawn in its own colors.
\f[B]cdu themes dump NAME\f[R] prints a theme\[cq]s YAML, to save as the
start of your own.
.TP
\f[B]cdu update\f[R]
Replace the running binary with the latest release from GitHub, after
verifying its checksum.
Reads only public release assets and sends nothing.
Skip it if cdu was installed by a package manager \[em] update through
that instead.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.PP
The Charm interface (the default) is driven by:
.TP
\f[B]\[ua] \[da], k j\f[R] / \f[B]g G\f[R] / \f[B]pgup pgdn\f[R]
Move the cursor / jump to top or bottom / page.
.TP
\f[B]\[->] \[CR] l\f[R] / \f[B]\[<-] h\f[R]
Enter the directory under the cursor / go to the parent (the ../ row
does too; at the scan root, \[<-] scans the directory above it on disk).
.TP
\f[B]/\f[R] / \f[B]f\f[R]
Filter this directory as you type (fuzzy, live) / find files by name
across the whole tree (glob or substring).
.TP
\f[B]s\f[R] / \f[B]t\f[R]
Sort menu (then a field: size, name, count, mtime; or \f[B]d\f[R] for
folders-first) / column menu (then \f[B]a\f[R] apparent size,
\f[B]B\f[R] bars, \f[B]c\f[R] count, \f[B]m\f[R] mtime; \f[B]s\f[R]
saves the view).
\f[B]a B c m\f[R] also work directly.
.TP
\f[B]p\f[R] / \f[B]i\f[R] / \f[B]v\f[R] / \f[B]o\f[R]
Theme picker (previews live) / toggle the item-info pane / view a file /
open a file in its default app.
.TP
\f[B]space\f[R] / \f[B]M\f[R] / \f[B]u\f[R]
Mark a row for a batch delete / open the delete queue / unmark all.
.TP
\f[B]d\f[R] / \f[B]D\f[R] / \f[B]e\f[R] / \f[B]U\f[R]
Trash (recoverable, does not free space) / delete permanently / empty a
file / undo the last trash.
A permission-denied delete offers to retry with sudo.
.TP
\f[B]r\f[R] / \f[B]T\f[R] / \f[B]F\f[R] / \f[B]?\f[R] / \f[B]esc\f[R] / \f[B]q\f[R]
Rescan / largest files / find duplicate files / help / back (cancel a
scan, or clear marks) / quit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
.PP
cdu reads a YAML config from \f[B]\[ti]/.config/cdu/cdu.yaml\f[R] (or
\f[B]$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/cdu/cdu.yaml\f[R]), overridden by
\f[B]--config-file\f[R].
On first run, if there is no cdu config but a gdu one exists, cdu reads
the gdu config read-only and says so; \f[B]--write-config\f[R] takes it
over into cdu\[cq]s own file.
.PP
Every persistent long flag is also a config key under its flag name
\[em] for example \f[B]show-apparent-size\f[R],
\f[B]show-item-count\f[R], \f[B]show-mtime\f[R],
\f[B]folders-first\f[R], \f[B]info\f[R] (the item pane, on by default),
\f[B]icons\f[R], \f[B]mouse\f[R], \f[B]no-hidden\f[R], and the
\f[B]ignore-dirs\f[R] list.
Two blocks have no single flag:
.TP
\f[B]sorting\f[R]
The default sort.
\f[B]by\f[R] is one of \f[I]name\f[R], \f[I]size\f[R],
\f[I]itemCount\f[R], \f[I]mtime\f[R]; \f[B]order\f[R] is \f[I]asc\f[R]
or \f[I]desc\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]theme\f[R]
Colours for the Charm interface (the classic interface is unaffected).
\f[B]preset\f[R] selects a bundled theme \[em] \f[I]charm\f[R],
\f[I]midnight\f[R], \f[I]ember\f[R], \f[I]phosphor\f[R], \f[I]mono\f[R]
\[em] and any token below it overrides that preset\[cq]s colour for one
role.
Tokens are \f[B]#rrggbb\f[R] only.
The roles include \f[I]accent\f[R], \f[I]text\f[R], \f[I]selected\f[R],
\f[I]danger\f[R], \f[I]size\f[R], \f[I]dim\f[R], and \f[I]panel\f[R].
A user theme file in \f[B]\[ti]/.config/cdu/themes/\f[R] is selected by
its filename with \f[B]--theme\f[R]; see \f[B]cdu themes\f[R].
.PP
The quickest start is \f[B]cdu --write-config\f[R], which writes the
effective configuration to edit.
Example:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
show-apparent-size: true
folders-first: true
sorting:
  by: size
  order: desc
theme:
  preset: midnight
  accent: \[dq]#ff8800\[dq]
\f[R]
.fi
.SH FILE FLAGS
.PP
Files and directories may be prefixed by a one-character flag with
following meaning:
.TP
\f[B]!\f[R]
An error occurred while reading this directory.
.TP
\f[B].\f[R]
An error occurred while reading a subdirectory, size may be not correct.
.TP
\f[B]\[at]\f[R]
File is symlink or socket.
.TP
\f[B]H\f[R]
Same file was already counted (hard link).
.TP
\f[B]e\f[R]
Directory is empty.
